{"lemma": "قَرْحٌ", "slug": "قَرْحٌ", "root": "ق.ر.ح", "root_slug": "ق-ر-ح", "root_link": "/words/roots/ق-ر-ح", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "قَرْح", "root": "قرح", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 3}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 5, "pos_tags": ["noun", "verb"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 5}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n35441"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%AD%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "ulcer", "fa": "زخم", "ur": "زخم", "tr": "yara", "id": "luka", "bn": "গলিত ক্ষত", "es": "úlcera", "fr": "ulcère", "de": "Geschwür", "ru": "язва", "zh": "溃疡"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to wound"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to ulcerate"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to wound"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "ulcer"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "plural of قُرْحَة (qurḥa)", "tags": ["form-of", "plural"]}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n35441", "headword_ar": "قَرْحٌ", "root": "qrH", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "quroHN", "text_ar": "قُرْحٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A wound;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L;) the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bite of a weapon,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of a similar thing that wounds the body:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, K: [but in some copies of the K, for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaD~u Als~ilaAHi wanaHowihi mim~aA yajoraHu Albadana", "text_ar": "عَضُّ السِّلَاحِ وَنَحْوِهِ مِمَّا يَجْرَحُ البَدَنَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(which is the reading in the CK), we find"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ED~ AlslAH wanaHowuhu", "text_ar": "عضّ السلاح وَنَحْوُهُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mm~A yaxoruju biAlbadani", "text_ar": "ممّا يَخْرُجُ بِالبَدَنِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and the L and TA combine the two readings, the latter whereof gives a second signification, which will be found below:])"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "juroHN", "text_ar": "جُرْحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[with which"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jaroHN", "text_ar": "جَرْحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is held by many to be syn.]: (TA:) they are two dial. vars., (S, Msb,) like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DaEofN", "text_ar": "ضَعْفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DuEofN", "text_ar": "ضُعْفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jahodN", "text_ar": "جَهْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "juhodN", "text_ar": "جُهْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Fr, Msb, TA,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wajodN", "text_ar": "وَجْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wujodN", "text_ar": "وُجْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Fr, TA;) the former of the dial. of El-Hijáz: (Msb:) or the former is an inf. n. and the latter is a simple subst.: (L, Msb:) or the former signifies as above; and the latter signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "its pain:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A:) or the latter seems to bear this latter signification; and the former, to signify"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "wounds"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "themselves: (Yaakoob, TA:) [and the like is said in the L and K:]) [and thus used in a pl. sense, the former is a coll. gen. n.;] and its n. un. is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaroHapN", "text_ar": "قَرْحَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "quruwHN", "text_ar": "قُرُوحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (L:) one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bihi quroHN mino qaroHK", "text_ar": "بِهِ قُرْحٌ مِنْ قَرْحٍ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "In him is pain from a wound;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A;) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from wounds."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaroHN", "text_ar": "قَرْحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Pustules,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "small swellings, when they have become corrupt;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, K;) [i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "purulent pustules;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "imposthumes, ulcers,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sores:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "quroHN", "text_ar": "قُرْحٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "accord. to the L and some copies of the K, as shown above; but this seems to be of doubtful authority:"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaroHN", "text_ar": "قَرْحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in this sense is a coll. gen. n.:] its n. un. is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaroHapN", "text_ar": "قَرْحَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "quruwHN", "text_ar": "قُرُوحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S.) Imra-el-Keys (the poet, TA) was called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*uw AlquruwHi", "text_ar": "ذُو القُرُوحِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because the King of the Greeks sent to him a poisoned shirt, from the wearing of which his body became affected with purulent pustules, or ulcers, or sores, ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "taqar~aHa", "text_ar": "تَقَرَّحَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) and he died: (S, K, * TA:) or, as some say, he was called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*uw AlfuruwjK", "text_ar": "ذُو الفُرُوجٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "f", "text_ar": "ف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "j", "text_ar": "ج"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; because he left only daughters. (Es-Suyootee, TA.) ―         -b3-  Also, (accord. to the K,) or ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "quroHN", "text_ar": "قُرْحٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (as in the L,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A severe scab"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mange, that destroys young weaned camels;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, K;) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that attacks young weaned camels, and from which they scarcely ever,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "never, recover:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so says Lth: Az, however, says that this is a mistake; but that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "quroHapN", "text_ar": "قُرْحَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies a certain disease that attacks camels, expl. below. (L.)       -A2-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qariyHN", "text_ar": "قَرِيحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 2511}], "source_refs": ["TA", "S", "Msb", "Fr", "L", "A"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}